description:
Planetary nebula Jones-Emberson 1 

For this image we really wanted to bring the 185mm to its knees.
We collected around 19 hours in Halpha and 15 hours in OIII and we drizzled both the channels reaching an outstanding resolution for a 185mm of around 0.45''/px.

CFF Telescopes APO 185mm f/6.8
Moravian Instruments 16200

Astro-Physics GTO 1100
Astrodon Ha 5nm: 58·1200s -30C bin 1x1
Astrodon O3 5nm: 46·1200s -30C bin 1x1

Copyright: Roberto Colombari / Mauro Narduzzi
________________________

Jones-Emberson 1 (PK 164+31.1), also known as the Headphone Nebula, is a 14th magnitude planetary nebula in the constellation Lynx at a distance of 1600 light years. It is a larger planetary with low surface brightness. The 16.8-magnitude central star is a very blue white dwarf.
Source: Wikipedia
title: Headphone Nebula
